                     <interp inst="t17750426-103-person845" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am Clerk to Sir 
               <persName id="t17750426-103-person846">
                  John
                   Fielding
               <interp inst="t17750426-103-person846" type="surname" value="Fielding"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750426-103-person846" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750426-103-person846" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This information, (producing it) I took down from the prisoner's mouth, after he was sworn an evidence for the crown; it was read over to him, and he signed it.</p>
               <p>"The information was read in court, in which he says; -</p>
               <p>"That Burdet, Clarke,</p>
               <p>"Davis, and himself, robbed the prosecutor</p>
               <p>"of a metal watch, &amp;c. and the Burdet sold</p>
               <p>"the watch."</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I spoke the truth when I was here, but when I was first taken up, I could not say the particulars of every thing. I spoke the truth as far as I could.</p>
